# FlexiUI - Cursor Rules

You are an expert senior developer working on FlexiUI, a modern React UI component library built with Tailwind CSS v4, published as individual npm packages in a pnpm monorepo managed by Nx.

## Project Context

- **Monorepo**: pnpm workspaces + Nx for build orchestration
- **Framework**: React 19+ with TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 + tailwind-variants (tv()) + BEM CSS classes
- **Accessibility**: React Aria Components (react-aria-components)
- **Testing**: Vitest
- **Storybook**: Component development & visual testing
- **Versioning**: Changesets
- **Package scope**: `@flexi-ui/*` - each component is a separate npm package

## Architecture Rules

### Component Pattern

Every component follows a **compound component pattern** (similar to Radix UI), built on top of **React Aria Components**:

```typescript
"use client";

import { createContext, useContext, forwardRef, useMemo } from "react";
import { Button as ButtonPrimitive } from "react-aria-components";
import { tv, cx, type VariantProps } from "tailwind-variants";

// 1. Styles in separate .styles.ts file
// 2. Context for compound components
// 3. Root component with forwardRef
// 4. Sub-components consuming context
// 5. Object.assign for compound export
// 6. Default export
```

### File Structure (per component package)

```
packages/components/component-name/
├── src/
│   ├── component-name.tsx        # Component implementation
│   ├── component-name.styles.ts  # Tailwind Variants (tv())
│   ├── main.ts                   # Barrel exports
│   └── use-component-name.ts     # Hook (if needed)
├── stories/
│   └── component-name.stories.tsx
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
└── vite.config.ts
```

### Styling Rules

1. **ALWAYS** define styles in `.styles.ts` files using `tv()` from `tailwind-variants`
2. **NEVER** use `twMerge` manually - `tailwind-variants` includes it
3. **ALWAYS** import from `tailwind-variants`, never from `@flexi-ui/standard`
4. CSS files use BEM naming: `.button`, `.button--primary`, `.button__icon`
5. Base classes include default size (md equivalent)
6. Medium variants (`--md`) are empty with comment

### CSS BEM Pattern

```css
.component {
  @apply [base-styles] [default-md-size];
}

.component--sm { @apply [small-overrides]; }
.component--md { /* No styles - default size */ }
.component--lg { @apply [large-overrides]; }
.component--primary { @apply [primary-styles]; }

.component__child { @apply [child-styles]; }
```

### Interactive States (REQUIRED for all interactive components)

```css
.component {
  &:hover, &[data-hovered="true"] { /* hover styles */ }
  &:active, &[data-pressed="true"] { /* pressed styles */ }
  &:focus-visible, &[data-focus-visible="true"] {
    outline: 2px solid var(--focus);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  &:disabled, &[aria-disabled="true"] {
    @apply pointer-events-none opacity-[var(--disabled-opacity)];
  }
}
```

### Export Pattern

```typescript
// Compound component
const CompoundComponent = Object.assign(ComponentRoot, {
  Item: ComponentItem,
  Trigger: ComponentTrigger,
  Content: ComponentContent,
});

export default CompoundComponent;
export type { ComponentRootProps, ComponentItemProps };
export { componentVariants, type ComponentVariants } from "./component.styles";
```

### React Aria Components className

- **Render prop components** (Button, Checkbox, etc.): Use `cx(styles, typeof className === 'function' ? className(renderProps) : className)`
- **String-only components** (Label, Input, etc.): Use `cx(styles, className)`
- **NEVER** use `composeTwRenderProps` or `twMerge` — `cx` from `tailwind-variants` handles merging

## Code Style

- Use `forwardRef` for all components
- Display names: `FlexiUI.ComponentName`
- Single quotes, no semicolons (per .prettierrc)
- Trailing commas everywhere
- 100 char print width
- Icons: Iconify with gravity-ui set (`@iconify/react`)

## Commit Convention

```
<type>(<scope>): <message>
```

Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, style, test, chore, ci

## Key Dependencies

- `react-aria-components` - Accessibility primitives
- `tailwind-variants` - Style variants with tv()
- `@flexi-ui/ripple` - Ripple effect (used by Button)
- `@flexi-ui/spinner` - Loading spinners
- `@flexi-ui/shared-utils` - Shared utilities
- `@flexi-ui/styles` - Shared CSS layer (BEM classes)

## Don'ts

- DON'T construct Tailwind class names dynamically (`bg-${color}-500`)
- DON'T create component-specific Label/Description components
- DON'T add documentation files unless explicitly asked
- DON'T use framer-motion (migrating away from it)
- DON'T put styles in component .tsx files - use .styles.ts
- DON'T use multiple @apply statements per CSS rule block
